
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ccm-ideas-identity-use-cases-02.txt'>
    <title>"Identity Use Cases in IDEAS", Uma Chunduri, Alexander Clemm, Michael Menth</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ccm-ideas-identity-use-cases-02.txt</link>
    <description>IDentity-EnAbled networkS (IDEAS) introduce the concept of Identity (IDy) into networking.  An IDy represents a high-level identifier representing a collection of identifiers of a device, node, or process used for communication purposes.  It is used for authentication purposes and never revealed in data plane packets. This document summarizes some conceptual use cases to illustrate the usefulness of IDEAS.</description>
    <dc:date>2017-10-10T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
